    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Phylum of about 70 wormlike species of ancient, terrestrial invertebrates with short, thick legs and a dry, velveteen-like body.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>含約七十種似蠕蟲的古老陸棲無脊椎動物；牠們的腿粗短，身體表面乾燥且如同天鵝絨。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stam van ongeveer 70 oude wormachtige soorten ongewervelde dieren die op het land leven en korte, dikke pootjes en een droog, fluweelachtig lichaam hebben.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
